About the job
Responsibilities

 About TikTok
TikTok is the leading destination for short-form mobile video. Our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. TikTok has global offices including Los Angeles, New York, London, Paris, Berlin, Dubai, Singapore, Jakarta, Seoul and Tokyo. 

Why Join Us
At TikTok, our people are humble, intelligent, compassionate and creative. We create to inspire - for you, for us, and for more than 1 billion users on our platform. We lead with curiosity and aim for the highest, never shying away from taking calculated risks and embracing ambiguity as it comes. Here, the opportunities are limitless for those who dare to pursue bold ideas that exist just beyond the boundary of possibility. Join us and make impact happen with a career at TikTok.

The Product Data Analytics Team analyses a combination of product usage and product performance data to derive meaningful insights that would serve as a guide to better product and decision making for our business leaders. The team will work through different business scenarios including improving Live app Experiences, Host Operation, User experiences. In addition, it is important to manage the data life cycle to ensure problems are quantitatively measured to propose logical solutions.

Responsibilities:
- Responsible for the data analytics work in international LIVE business, including but not limited to live gifts, host interaction, strategies, enhancing the live-streaming revenue;
- Analyse the key factors for the current growth of international LIVE, find improvements points through data and provide data basis and judgment for the next iteration of the business;
- Develop a deep understanding of the business logic and user request scenarios of international LIVE, design a reasonable indicator system based on business objectives, evaluate and monitor business performance quickly and effectively, and give valuable decision-making suggestions through in-depth analysis and mining of indicators;
- Be deeply engaged in the construction of international LIVE business, analyse and sort out business logic, disassemble the analysis planning and construction system based on goals, output indicator system and diagnosis mechanism
- Evaluate and monitor business performance in an effective and quick manner;
- Cooperate with the business teams (product/operation/RD) to initiate special data projects or phased data recaps, local internal optimisation points through data induction and analysis, promote the implementation of improvement plans, and obtain actual benefits. 

Qualifications

 1. Bachelor degree or above in Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics or other related majors;
2. At least 3 years of experiences and above; Experience in supporting analytical work of internet or large scale C2C products is preferred;
3. Proficient in SQL, skilled use of visualisation tools
4. Experience in data extraction, analysis and visualisation in a complex data environment, and have experiences in data landing to the business
5. Excellent communication skills with ability to communicate conclusions effectively to both technical and non-technical audiences, and good analysis report writing ability;
6. Strong learning ability and curiosity driven mindset, independent and possess collaborative problem solving skills

TikTok is committed to creating an inclusive space where employees are valued for their skills, experiences, and unique perspectives. Our platform connects people from across the globe and so does our workplace. At TikTok, our mission is to inspire creativity and bring joy. To achieve that goal, we are committed to celebrating our diverse voices and to creating an environment that reflects the many communities we reach. We are passionate about this and hope you are too.

About the job
Who Are We?

At HoYoverse, we are committed to creating immersive virtual world experiences for players around the world. In addition to game products such as Genshin Impact, Honkai Impact 3rd, Tears of Themis, and Honkai: Star Rail, HoYoverse also launched the dynamic desktop software N0va Desktop, the community product HoYoLAB, and created a variety of products such as animations, comics, music, novels, and merchandise around our original creative concept.

Adhering to our mission of Tech Otakus Save the World, we have always been committed to technology research and development, exploring cutting-edge technologies, and have accumulated leading technical capabilities in cartoon rendering, artificial intelligence, cloud gaming technology, and other fields.

HoYoverse is actively engaged in globalization, with offices in Singapore, Montreal, Los Angeles, Tokyo, Seoul, and other areas.

When you apply to a position with HoYoverse, we will process your personal data. To learn more about how we process your data, we encourage you to review our comprehensive Global Applicant and Candidate Privacy Policy. This policy provides detailed insights into how your information is collected, used, and protected throughout the application process.

What You Will Do: 
Play an important role by providing product analysis to help in decision making as well as to ensure the long-term operations of the product with your data ability;
Establish and improve data monitoring and analyzing systems;
Provide data support to product design, operational analysis, content effect evaluation, player behavior analysis and community opinions analysis through data analysis or mathematical modeling.
What We Are Looking For: 
Loyal game players, basic understanding of the gaming industry, familiar with various video games;
Extensive gameplay experience with HoYoverse Games is a plus;
Proficiency in SQL and data analysis tools including Excel, SPSS, Python or SAS;
Familiar with common data mining model (for example, clustering, regression, decision tree);
Sensitive to data, possess a strong learning ability, strong logical and analytical capabilities, and project execution skills, and able to communicate with designers and developers;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English and fluent oral Chinese to liaise with teams.
We are an equal opportunity employer that believes diverse backgrounds are key to bringing our concepts to life. If you're looking to play a key role in creating the best immersive virtual world experience for our users, we invite you to join our team.

About the job
Responsibilities

Founded in 2012, ByteDance's mission is to inspire creativity and enrich life. With a suite of more than a dozen products, including TikTok, Helo, and Resso, as well as platforms specific to the China market, including Toutiao, Douyin, and Xigua, ByteDance has made it easier and more fun for people to connect with, consume, and create content.

Why Join Us

At ByteDance, our people are humble, intelligent, compassionate and creative. We create to inspire - for you, for us, and for millions of users across all of our products. We lead with curiosity and aim for the highest, never shying away from taking calculated risks and embracing ambiguity as it comes. Here, the opportunities are limitless for those who dare to pursue bold ideas that exist just beyond the boundary of possibility. Join us and make impact happen with a career at ByteDance.

We Are Hiring For Stellar Data Analyst/Senior Data Analyst For The Space Systems And Analytics Team. We Cover 4 Pillars Of Work:

 RE&F (Real Estate & Facilities) Management System: Coordinate the system requirements of each module in RE&F, plan the system architecture and functions, prioritize classifications based on business importance and business;
 Employee Side System Management: Online RE&F services (such as moving seat selection, workstation reservation, equipment maintenance, workplace information viewing, etc) to improve employee work efficiency and experience;
 Data Management and Analysis: Access company-related system data sources, maintain RE&F data warehouse. Build RE&F data index system. Complete various thematic data analysis and forecasting.
 Data Products: Output customised data products such as reports, dashboard, visualize screens. In order to intuitively present, track and warn data on topics such as space efficiency, cost, and project schedule.


Responsibilities:

 Responsible for the set-up of business indicator systems for Real Estate leasing projects, facility management, space planning, cost management, etc., attribution of short-term anomalies and analysis of long-term trends and providing valuable suggestions with reports;
 Build dashboards based on the indicator systems and establish a daily tracker and monitoring system to promptly identify relevant trends or potential blockers;
 Perform various data analysis according to business needs, quickly locate internal problems or discover opportunities through keen insight into data, qualitative and quantitative analysis, and modeling;
 Maintain smooth and effective communication with internal stakeholders, such as the Real Estate, Product, R&D, Algorithm, and other teams to ensure the implementation and continuous optimization of data analysis conclusions and to build data systems and user-friendly data products to support business.


Qualifications

Requirements:

 Strong in mathematics, statistics, computer science, data science/statistics, engineering and related majors;
 Proficiency in SQL, Tableau, familiar with Python or R for data analysis Algorithm (ML. causal inference), dynamic programming background is a plus.
 Experienced in data analysis, rich data mining, information collection, and analysis capabilities, strong ability to translate business problem into data modeling;
 Solid communication and collaboration skills and the ability to work effectively with internal teams;
 Have a strong learning ability and curiosity; ability to quickly pick up domain knowledge in new areas; Can lead a small project team to support business;


