About the Team
The Monetization Integrity Operations team plays a critical role in driving initiatives to mitigate risks in Ads and ensuring advertiser quality on our platform. The team also provides efficient and high quality reviews to unlock good revenue and focus on brand safety and user/Advertister experience. 

We are looking for talented individuals to join us for an internship in 2023. Internships at TikTok aim to offer students industry exposure and hands-on experience. Watch your ambitions become reality as your inspiration brings infinite opportunities at TikTok.

Please state your availability clearly in your resume (Start date, End date).

Candidates can apply to a maximum of two positions and will be considered for jobs in the order you apply. The application limit is applicable to TikTok and its affiliates' jobs globally. Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis - we encourage you to apply early.

About the Role
We are looking for an intern to join the crowdsourcing team. He/she needs to have a strong sense of ownership and ability to deliver with minimal guidance. He/she will be expected to build ETL pipelines, interface with cross team applications/ stakeholders and perform in-depth statistical analysis. He/ she will own the entire technical portion of the crowdsourcing team. 

Responsibilities
- Provide the technical support for crowdsourcing project;
- Plan and design the quality assurance and payment pipeline;
- Interface with stakeholders like our Labelling Platform to enable functions like auto data injection;
- Manage the upstream and downstream hive table relationship;
- Build dashboards to demonstrate the key metrics of labeller performance;
- Work with AI research team to integrate machine learning models for automation solutions;
- Send and fetch the data through APIs to and from different stakeholders;
- Document progress and finding to present to leadership and enable smooth handover;
- Derive key insights from the results of projects to optimize the labelling process. 

Qualifications

 - Undergraduate, or Postgraduate who is currently pursuing a degree/master in Statistics, Big Data, Computer Science or another quantitative field;
- Experience building high-quality end-to-end data solutions in an agile environment from requirements to production;
- Be able to proactively handle prioritization of work and deliver work of great quality and to influence the broader team;
- Experience with Tableau, Power Bl, or other business intelligence platforms;
- Experience with writing and optimizing SQL, and with one general purpose programming language, such as Python;
- Strong experience with ETL tools and processes;
- Experience with APIs.

